25-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAlbert%20Edwards%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20shows%20the%20US%20unemployment%20rate%20(in%20red)%20alongside%20its%20three-year%20moving%20average%20(dotted%20line).%20Since%201950%2C%20in%20eight%20instances%20where%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20has%20begun%20an%20uptrend%20and%20broken%20through%20its%20three-year%20moving%20average%2C%20a%20recession%20has%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221734%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22unemployment%20rate%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695eb78c04eda4732f2ea8d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22788%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESociete%20Generale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRecession%20is%20the%20biggest%20threat%20to%20equities%2C%20although%20in%20recent%20downturns%20financial%20problems%20have%20preceded%20(or%20caused)%20recessions%2C%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20wrote%20in%20the%20note.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20any%20guru%20is%20forecasting%20a%20recession%20in%202026.%20Yet%20the%20simple%20correlation%20shown%20below%20has%20a%20100%25%20track%20record%20of%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chart%20mirrors%20the%20concept%20of%20the%20Sahm%20Rule%20Recession%20Indicator%2C%20which%20says%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20in%20a%20recession%20when%20the%20three-month%20moving%20average%20of%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20increases%20by%20more%20than%200.5%25%20from%20its%20lows%20over%20the%20previous%2012%20months.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20if%20unemployment%20rises%20too%20quickly%2C%20it%20signals%20that%20things%20are%20about%20to%20get%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20had%20been%20hailed%20for%20its%20back-tested%20accuracy%20since%20its%20release%20in%202019%2C%20the%20gauge%20produced%20its%20first%20false%20reading%20in%20August%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22sahm%20rule%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695eb77464858d02d217ef64%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22465%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESt.%20Louis%20Fed%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20if%20the%20labor%20market%20weakens%20materially%2C%20as%20Edwards'%20chart%20suggests%20could%20happen.%20Hiring%20rates%20and%20job%20openings%20remain%20sluggish.%20But%20other%20important%20measures%20of%20the%20economy's%20health%20%E2%80%94%20like%20consumer%20spending%20and%20GDP%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20remain%20strong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20signal%20that%20a%20recession%20could%20be%20on%20the%20way%2C%20according%20to%20Edwards%2C%20is%20a%20steepening%20of%20the%20Treasury%20yield%20curve%20following%20its%20inversion.%20However%2C%20while%20falling%20short-term%20rates%20following%20an%20inversion%20are%20usually%20accompanied%20by%20a%20floundering%20job%20market%20and%20consumer%2C%20today's%20economy%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20a%20stronger%20starting%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-unemployment-chart-downturn-sahm-rule-wall-street-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767868202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695ec1e8832e0ef1ead75ca2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-unemployment-chart-downturn-sahm-rule-wall-street-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Recession%20fears%20have%20cooled%2C%20but%20a%20labor%20market%20chart%20flagged%20by%20one%20bearish%20strategist%20might%20give%20bullish%20investors%20pause.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-unemployment-chart-downturn-sahm-rule-wall-street-2026-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22